	<hr>
	@subsection		konalheplus		KONA LHe Plus

	This page describes the KONA LHe Plus video capture/playout board.
	It’s identified by ::DEVICE_ID_KONALHEPLUS.

	@image	html	konalheplus.png

	The KONA LHe+ board has a breakout connector on the far left, then the SDI input (J2),
	SDI output 1 (J3), and SDI output 2 (J4).

	@par	PCI Interface

	-	PCI device ID: <b>0xDB05</b>
	-	Four-lane gen 2 PCI Express
	-	2 DMA engines
	-	Legacy interrupt delivery (INTA\# for all interrupts) — MSI not supported

	@par	Inputs & Outputs

	-	1 × SDI input
	-	2 × SDI outputs
	-	1 × analog component video input
	-	1 × analog component video output
	-	1 × reference/LTC input
	-	1 × LTC output
	-	1 × RS-422 serial port

	@par	Frame Buffer

	-	256 MB SDRAM
	-	32 × 8MB frames

	@par	Audio

	-	1 audio system
	-	8 channels (max.) per audio system
	-	2 channels (max.) of AES audio (input and output)
	-	Audio system’s 8MB buffer memory starts at first byte of last frame
	-	AES audio inputs support asynchronous audio, 32Hz-96kHz, sample-rate converted to 48kHz
	-	AES audio outputs

	@par	Video Formats

	-	Supports most standard video formats.
	-	Does not support DVCPro HD or HDV.
	-	RGB is not supported.

	@par	Video Processing

	-	1 mixer/keyer, with Mix Coefficient and Wipe Generator
	-	Compression widget

	@par	Ancillary Data

	-	\ref vancframegeometries only

	@par	External Connectivity

	-	Optional \ref aja101884 provides access to other inputs and outputs
	-	Optional \ref ajaklboxlh provides convenient access to the board's inputs and outputs in a 1U rack-mountable chassis.

	@par	SDK Support

	-	Since before 2009 in <a href="https://sdksupport.aja.com/index.php?/Knowledgebase/Article/View/3">SDK v2.1 (MacOS)</a>.

	@par	Firmware
	<https://sdksupport.aja.com/index.php?/Knowledgebase/Article/View/142/25>
